{"name": "maypy", "metadata": {"name": "maypy", "version": "1.1.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Topic :: Utilities", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Pythonic Java optional", "upload_time": 1729346741}, "documentation": ["<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin:40px;\">\n  <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/MLetrone/maypy/master/docs/pages/assets/img/logo.png\" alt=\"Maypy logo\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 2rem\" width=\"300\"/>\n<!-- --8<-- [start:overview-header] -->\n\n  [![Language](https://img.shields.io/badge/Language-python\u22653.9-3776ab?style=flat-square&logo=Python)](https://www.python.org/)\n  ![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow?style=flat-square)\n  ![Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/Style-ruff-9a9a9a?style=flat-square)\n  ![Lint](https://img.shields.io/badge/Lint-ruff,%20mypy-brightgreen?style=flat-square)\n  [![Tests](https://github.com/MLetrone/maypy/actions/workflows/check.yml/badge.svg?branch=master)](https://github.com/MLetrone/maypy/actions/workflows/check.yml)\n\n<!-- --8<-- [end:overview-header] -->\n\n---\n\nSource Code: [https://github.com/MLetrone/maypy](https://github.com/MLetrone/maypy)\n\ndocumentation: [https://mletrone.github.io/maypy](https://mletrone.github.io/maypy/)\n\n---\n</div>\n<!-- --8<-- [start:overview-body] -->\n\nMaypy is python implementation of the well known Java [Optional](https://docs.oracle.com/en%2Fjava%2Fjavase%2F11%2Fdocs%2Fapi%2F%2F/java.base/java/util/Optional.html) API.\nIt's designed to help you handle potential `None` values, reducing error from `NoneType`.\n\n## Features :\n- Brings functional programming\n- Easy to use\n- Fully typed and compatible with `mypy` !\n- Lightweight\n\n<!-- --8<-- [end:overview-body] -->\n## installation\n\n```shell\npip install maypy\n```\n\nThat's all ! _Ready to use_\n\n## Usage\n\n### Description\n\n<!-- --8<-- [start:description] -->\n\nIt's not rare to handle return from function that _maybe_ either a value or None.\nLike `.get` from a dictionary, results from api or ORM etc.\nWith no more `if value is None` with `MayPy`, encapsulate your value and do what you want to.\n\nMayPy brings `Maybe` a wrapper (container), it is either **empty** if the value passed was `None` or valuated,\nin this case it contains the value, and we can perform operation on it.\n\n<!-- --8<-- [end:description] -->\n\n### Examples\n\nChecking value presence:\n```python\nfrom maypy import Maybe\n\nassert Maybe.empty().is_empty()\nassert Maybe.of(None).is_empty()\nassert Maybe.of(\"value\").is_present()\n```\nUsing chaining operation over wrapped value:\n```python\nfrom maypy import Maybe\nfrom typing import List, Optional\n\n\ndef convert_to_celsius(fahrenheit: float) -> float:\n  return (fahrenheit - 32) * 5 / 9\n\n\nfahrenheit_temperatures: List[Optional[float]] = [32.45, None, 26.6, 100, 72, None, 10]\n\nfor temp in fahrenheit_temperatures:\n  Maybe.of(temp).map(convert_to_celsius).filter(lambda celsius: celsius > 0)\n```\n\nDefining return from database result:\n\n````python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom enum import StrEnum, unique\n\nfrom maypy import Maybe\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import Session\n\n\n@unique\nclass Gender(StrEnum):\n  MALE = \"M\"\n  FEMALE = \"F\"\n  UNKNOWN = \"X\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass User:\n  id: str\n  email: str\n  gender: Gender\n\n\nclass UserEntity(BaseModel):\n  id: str\n  email: str\n  gender: str\n\n  class Config:\n    orm_mode = True\n\n\ndef get_user(db: Session, user_id: str) -> Maybe[User]:\n  return Maybe.of(db.query(UserEntity).filter(UserEntity.id == user_id).first()).map(to_domain)\n\n\ndef to_domain(user_dto: UserEntity) -> User:\n  return User(\n    id=user_dto.id,\n    email=user_dto.email,\n    gender=Gender(user_dto.gender)\n  )\n\n\nuser = get_user(db, \"481efz4x1d\").or_else_raise(Exception(\"User id<481efz4x1d> not found\"))\n````"], "modules": [{"name": "maypy._functional", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "maypy._functional.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._functional.V", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._functional.T_MAPPER", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "maypy._functional.Predicate", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._functional.Predicate.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Predicate logic."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Protocol describing predicate function.\n\nThe corresponding signature is `Callable[[T], bool]`.\n\nIts goal is to verify if a value `T` match the conditions define.\n(can be a named function or lambda function).\n\nExamples:\n    >>> lambda string: bool(string) and bool(string.strip())\n    >>> # OR\n    >>> from typing import Sequence\n    >>>\n    >>> def is_empty(seq: Sequence) -> bool:\n    >>>     return len(seq) == 0"]}, {"name": "maypy._functional.Mapper", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._functional.Mapper.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "V", "xref": {"fqname": "V", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Mapping logic."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Protocol describing mapper function.\n\nThe corresponding signature is `Callable[[T], V]`.\n\nIts goal is to transform a value to another.\n(can be a named function or lambda function).\n\nExamples:\n    >>> lambda val: val * 15\n    >>> # OR\n    >>> from numbers import Number\n    >>> def multiply_by_ten(val: int) -> int:\n    >>>     return 10 * val"]}, {"name": "maypy._functional.Supplier", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._functional.Supplier.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "V", "xref": {"fqname": "V", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Supply logic."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Protocol describing supplier function.\n\nThe corresponding signature is `Callable[[], None]`.\n\nIts goal is to supply a new `V` value at invocation.\n(can be a named function or lambda function).\n\nExamples:\n    >>> lambda: list(range(5))\n    >>> # OR\n    >>> def create_list() -> list[int]:\n    >>>     return list(range(5))"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "maypy", "documentation": ["Maypy package."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "maypy.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "maypy.Empty", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Empty", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.EmptyMaybeException", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._exceptions.EmptyMaybeException", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.Mapper", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._functional.Mapper", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.MaybeException", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._exceptions.MaybeException", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.Predicate", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._functional.Predicate", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.predicates", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy.predicates", "project": null}}, {"name": "maypy.Supplier", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._functional.Supplier", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "maypy._exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "maypy._exceptions.MaybeException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base exception for Maybe."]}, {"name": "maypy._exceptions.EmptyMaybeException", "bases": ["MaybeException"], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._exceptions.EmptyMaybeException.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception warning that the maybe contains no value to get."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "maypy._maybe.VALUE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.OUTPUT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Empty", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "bases": ["ABC"], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.empty", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Returns a empty `Maybe` instance."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.of", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Returns a `Maybe` instance depends on the value provided.\n\nIf it's a none value, an empty `Maybe` will be returned.\n\nParams:\n    val: the provided value to wrap.\n\nReturns:\n    A Maybe containing the value, if non-None value, otherwise an empty Maybe."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the value if present, else raise EmptyElementException.\n\nReturns:\n    The non-None value contained in this Maybe.\n\nRaises:\n    EmptyElementException: if no value present."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "predicate", "type": {"name": "Predicate", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Predicate", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Filter the wrapped value (if present).\n\nIf it matches the predicate, returns a Maybe describing the value,\notherwise return an empty Maybe.\n\nArgs:\n    predicate: predicate function to apply to the value.\n\nReturns:\n    A Maybe containing the value if it matched the predicate, else an empty Maybe."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mapper", "type": {"name": "Mapper", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Mapper", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "OUTPUT", "xref": {"fqname": "OUTPUT", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "OUTPUT", "xref": {"fqname": "OUTPUT", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Map the wrapped value (if present).\n\nApply the given mapping function to the value.\n\nArgs:\n    mapper: mapping function to apply to the value.\n\nReturns:\n    A Maybe containing the result of applying the mapping function on the value,\n    if value is present else an empty Maybe."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.or_else", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Supplier", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Supplier", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Returns the value if present, else return other.\n\nIf other is a supplier, it returns the result of the invocation.\n\nArgs:\n    other: value to be return if no value present.\n        if other is a supplier function, returns the invocation instead.\n\nReturns:\n    The value held by this Maybe if non-None value, otherwise either other or other invocation."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.or_none", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Returns the value if present, else return None.\n\nReturns:\n    The value held by this `Maybe` if non-None value, otherwise None."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.or_else_raise", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exception", "type": {"name": "Exception", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.Exception", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Returns the value if present, otherwise raise the given exception.\n\nArgs:\n    exception: The exception to be raised if no value present."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.is_present", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Returns True if value is present, otherwise False."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.is_empty", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Returns True if value is not present, otherwise False."]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe.Maybe.if_present", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "consumer", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Invoke the given consumer with the value if present, do nothing otherwise.\n\nArgs:\n    consumer: function to be executed if value present."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Wrapper class inspired by the well-known Optional API from Java.\n\nA Maybe is container, a non-none value may be inside or may be not\n(hence the name Maybe as an alternative to Optional, which is already used by Python).\n\nIf a value is present: `is_present` will return True and `get` will return the value.\n\n\nIt useful when working with data that can be none.\n\nExamples:\n    >>> import json\n    >>> beer = json.loads(json_beer)\n    >>> # Without maybe\n    >>> price = beer.get(\"BeerPrice\")\n    >>> if price:\n    >>>     if price > 0:\n    >>>         price = convertDollarsToEuro(price)\n    >>> else:\n    >>>     raise MyCustomException()\n    >>> #  with Maybe\n    >>> Maybe.of(beer.get(\"BeerPrice\")).\n    >>>     filter(lambda price: price > 0).\n    >>>     map(convertDollarsToEuro).\n    >>>     or_else_raise(MyCustomException())\n    >>>"]}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "predicate", "type": {"name": "Predicate", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Predicate", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mapper", "type": {"name": "Mapper", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Mapper", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "OUTPUT", "xref": {"fqname": "OUTPUT", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Maybe", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe.Maybe", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "OUTPUT", "xref": {"fqname": "OUTPUT", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.or_else", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Supplier", "xref": {"fqname": "maypy._maybe._functional.Supplier", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "maypy._maybe._ValuedMaybe.or_none", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "VALUE", "xref": {"fqname": "VALUE", "p